frameDefinitions: An Event continues at a certain Place through Time.
In this frame, an Agent or Cause changes the duration of an Event.
A Cognizer computes a Result on the basis of input Numbers by addition.
An Entity began its existence in the context of a Origin, which can be a place,  culture, time period, text, etc.
The absolute Value of a quantifiable Attribute  of an item is determined by adding up the values for the Attribute of the individuals or parts that make up the item.
A Part is considered to be a member of the set described by the Total.
frameExamples: Pyongyang agreed to suspend its withdrawal while talks <t>continued</t> with Washington.
Don't let him <t>prolong</t> the discussion to an absurd length.
The Christian <t>origin</t> of this quote is from Isaiah 22.
Defence is provided in West Germany by armed forces whose number <t>totals</t> close to half a million men and women
Dr. Nelson <t>numbers</t> among the world?s foremost geotechnical engineering experts.
